<TITLE> Brig Gen Arif new SKS MD </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka May 7 (bdnews24.com)The government on Thursday shuffled a few army officers deputed to the civil administration. Brigadier General Arif Ahmed Chowdhury was appointed managing director to Sena Kalyan Sangstha. His predecessor, Brigadier General Hamid Al Hasan, was brought back to the army, according to the establishment ministry. Chief engineer of Dhaka City Corporation Colonel Ashfaqul Islam will swap his position with engineer adviser to defence ministry Col Abdul Quadir. Major Zamil Hossain Munshi was appointed assistant survey superintendent of the survey department. A prior order appointing Maj Abu Arif Manwarul Islam to the position was cancelled. Meanwhile, joint secretary Abu Alam Shahid Khan was promoted to additional secretary. bd
